Sorry, `spark.hadoop.*` is for `SparkConf` and are static. What I really meant is Hadoop properties that are set directly in Spark SQL. They won't be propagated.

```
private[sql] object SessionState {
  def newHadoopConf(hadoopConf: Configuration, sqlConf: SQLConf): Configuration = {
    val newHadoopConf = new Configuration(hadoopConf)
    sqlConf.getAllConfs.foreach { case (k, v) => if (v ne null) newHadoopConf.set(k, v) }
    newHadoopConf
  }
}
```

The performance concern, though, is valid. Especially, in `ReadTask`. Let's keep it as is.

